      • testConditionalLazyEval

        public void testConditionalLazyEval()
                             throws ParseException,
                                    EvaluateException
        Test that for a conditional ternary operator expr 'a ? b : c' where evaluation of 'c' results in an Evaluation exception. This is to check that we are lazily evaluating the 'b' and 'c' expressions.
        Throws:
        ParseException - if the expression cannot parse correctly
        EvaluateException - if the expression fail its evaluation
